Reasoning: The paper presents a novel object tracking method that employs an instance-specific objectness measure and updates the object model during the tracking process. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as object detection and tracking, and machine learning (ML) techniques such as learning to re-rank proposals. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves ML techniques such as instance-specific objectness measure and learning to re-rank proposals, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories. The paper also involves robotics (RO) techniques such as tracking moving objects, which makes cs.RO a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves multimedia (MM) techniques such as processing low-frame-rate videos, which makes cs.MM a possible sub-category.
